QA Report – Diaspora Platform
1. Login Form Validation Issue
Severity: Critical
Area: Authentication
Issue: Login form allows submission without password
Impact: Poor UX, unnecessary backend requests
2. Password Reset for Non-Existent Account
Severity: Medium
Area: Authentication
“If you have an account, an email has been sent with password reset instructions.”
3. Password Reset Link Broken / Expired
Severity: Critical
Area: Authentication
Issue: Password reset link fails for registered accounts with:

“Link expired or invalid. Please request a new one.”

Impact: Blocks account recovery
4. Weak Passwords Allowed
Severity: High
Area: Authentication / Security
Issue: Users can create an account with a one-digit password
Impact: Security risk
5. Account Page – Address Not Updating
Severity: High
Area: User Profile / Checkout
Issue: Adding a shipping address does not update the display; it still shows:

“No default shipping address set. + Add Default Address”

Impact: Confusing for users, may block checkout
6. Cart – Increment Lag
Severity: Medium
Area: UX / Performance
Issue: Incrementing item quantity in the cart feels laggy
Impact: Poor user experience, may frustrate users
7. Checkout – Delivery Profile Not Recognized
Severity: Critical
Area: Checkout / Profile
Issue: Even with a shipping address added, the system prompts:

“Please complete your delivery profile first”

Impact: Users cannot proceed to checkout, blocking purchases













For security reasons, many developers use the "Anti-Enumeration" pattern (which you already have in your code), where you return a success message regardless of whether the email exists. This prevents hackers from guessing which emails are registered on your site



